w:pPr><w:r><w:t>Introduction</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="442A70CD" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00F018BB" w:rsidRDefault="00000000"><w:r><w:t>Student engagement plays an important role in the effectiveness of the learning process. In traditional classrooms, instructors usually rely on visual observation to judge whether students are attentive, distracted, or disengaged. However, continuously monitoring the attention level of every student can be challenging, especially in large classes. Recent developments in artificial intelligence and computer vision make it possible to automatically analyze visual information from classroom environments. By examining facial expressions, head orientation, and surrounding objects, AI systems can estimate whether students are focused on the lecture. The goal of this project is to design an AI‑based solution that evaluates student attention levels using image analysis and deep learning techniques. The proposed system aims to assist instructors by providing an automated overview of classroom engagement.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="2B362ED5" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00F018BB" w:rsidRDefault="00000000"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading1"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>Literature Review</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="58AF6A5C" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00F018BB" w:rsidRDefault="00000000"><w:r><w:t>The following table summarizes recent research (published after 2022) related to student engagement detection using computer vision and deep learning techniques.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:tbl><w:tblPr><w:tblW w:w="8640" w:type="dxa"/><w:tblBorders><w:top w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/><w:left w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/><w:bottom w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/><w:right w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/><w:insideH w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/><w:insideV w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/></w:tblBorders><